{{DISPLAYTITLE:iSCSI}}

iSCSI is a software platform used in storage area networks (SANs) to connect storage devices via ethernet connection to a server.

This article acts as a portal to iSCSI sub-articles.

* [[iSCSI/Initiator|iSCSI Initiator]] - The Initiator connects to a storage machine on the network.
* [[iSCSI/Target|iSCSI Target]] - The storage machine itself.

